reviews.review: It was so deeply silly from the opening to the very end.

The Star Wars franchise has jumped the Sarlacc.  The movie was thin gruel with a forced plot relying on old SW tropes replayed.  Clones ad Phantom Menace just moved a spot up from worst and second worst additions to the family.
It wasnt to bad wish it could of had more to it. Would recommend to watch.
Have some problems but this new trilogy its a trash, after all its a fun movie and don't disrespect the fans although nothing came of it.

It's not great but it's not terrible. Had some good callbacks, but it suffers from horrible plot planning when analyzed in line with the rest of the sequel trilogy and even the whole Skywalker Saga as a whole.

I really enjoyed it. A little rough around the edges to start, but once it found its legs it took off running and never slowed down. Wrapped up loose ends I had forgotten were out there. Not a perfect movie, but an enjoyable one that, for me, was a satisfying end to the saga. And my kids loved it (11 and 9)
I cried when all the ships showed up, Adam Driver is a god, I'm so glad I didn't die before I got to see this, totally awesome thank you so much...

Hard to wrap up three trilogies and countless unanswered questions about the Star Wars universe, but I thought it was hugely entertaining and sentimental . It touched the heart strings with old and new characters, maybe a little cheesy at times, but Star Wars has always been a little cheesy. I liked the new things about the Sith and Force ghosts that were revealed. Thank goodness there wasnt another Death Star. The last battles and Kylos transformation were a bit rushed, but were overall satisfying.

No es una buena película, es muy mala, una mezcla de ocurrencias y situaciones queriendo corregir el daño que causó el Episodio 8... La verdad es que no culpo completamente de este disparate a JJ Abrams, entiendo que era una situación insalvable, y que hizo lo que se pudo para devolverle un poco de respeto a la saga, pero eso no quita que sea una mala película.
Got what I needed from it :)
